    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the **Stepper** compound component:\n\n---\n\n## What will be created\n\n### 3 New Files\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | Component (7 sub-components) |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | Horizontal demo |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-vertical-demo.tsx` | Vertical demo |\n\n### 2 Registry Appends (no existing content modified)\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` | Append 1 `stepper` entry |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` | Append 2 example entries |\n\n---\n\n## Component Architecture\n\n**Two React contexts** (following the `ToggleGroup` pattern):\n- `StepperContext` — root-level: `{ orientation, activeStep, onStepChange }`\n- `StepperItemContext` — per-step: `{ step, state: \"active\"|\"completed\"|\"inactive\", disabled }`\n\n**7 sub-components:**\n\n| Component | Element | Key behavior |\n|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root; holds state (controlled + uncontrolled); `group/stepper` class |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Computes own `state` from context; sets `data-state` + provides item context |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Circle indicator (number → highlighted → ✓); calls `onStepChange` on click |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | Dims when inactive; uses `data-[state=active]:text-foreground` |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | Always muted (like `CardDescription`) |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Placed **between** `<StepperItem>` nodes as a sibling; accepts `afterStep` prop; turns primary when completed |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Hidden via `hidden` attribute + `data-[state=active]:block` |\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n- **No Radix UI** — pure semantic HTML like `Breadcrumb`, not like `Accordion`\n- **Separator is a sibling**, not a child of `StepperItem` (mirrors `<BreadcrumbSeparator>` in `<BreadcrumbList>`) — this is critical for horizontal layout\n- **Orientation via CSS groups** — children use `group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:` selectors; no prop-drilling\n- **`data-disabled={disabled ? \"\" : undefined}`** — never `data-disabled=\"false\"` (a truthy string that would wrongly match the selector)\n- **`lucide-react`** listed as a dependency (for `CheckIcon`), consistent with `sidebar` and `chart` entries\n\n---\n\n## Verification Steps\n1. `pnpm tsc --noEmit` — no TypeScript errors in new files\n2. `pnpm registry:build` — `stepper`, `stepper-demo`, `stepper-vertical-demo` appear in `registry.json`\n3. Dev server — both demos render; clicking steps/buttons transitions state correctly; focus ring visible on tab",
